<h1 class="Article-title">Breadcrumbs</h1>
<p class="Text--lead">Easily create nice looking breadcrumbs in different styles</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="section:usage"><a href="#section:usage" class="Text--resetLink">Usage</a></h2>

<p>The breadcrumb component consists of a <code>.Breadcrumbs</code> parent component which is in a <code>nav</code> tag. This wraps a <code>.Breadcrumbs-list</code> list tag with children that have the <code>.Breadcrumbs-item</code> class.</p>

<p>Variables in component.breadcrumbs.definition.scss give you control over a great deal of parameters include spacer icon, spacing and text decoration.</p>

<p>This component is based on the <a href="http://foundation.zurb.com/sites/docs/breadcrumbs.html" target="_blank">Foundation breadcrumb component</a> using <a href="https://schema.org/docs/gs.html" target="_blank">microdata</a> <a href="https://developers.google.com/search/docs/data-types/breadcrumbs">recommendations from Google for breadcrumbs</a> to improve SEO. It also includes ARIA labels to let visually impared users know where they are and what the current breadcrumb item is.</p>

<p>Microformats meta can be validated using <a href="https://search.google.com/structured-data/testing-tool" target="_blank">this Google tool.</a></p>

